TY  - JOUR
AU  - Kopányi-Peuker, Anita
AU  - Weber, Matthias
T1  - Experience Does Not Eliminate Bubbles: Experimental Evidence
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa121
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 9
SP  - 4450
EP  - 4485
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study the role of investor experience in the formation of asset price bubbles. We conduct a call market experiment in which participants trade assets with each other and a learning-to-forecast experiment in which participants only forecast future prices (while trade based on these forecasts is computerized). Each experiment comprises three treatments varying the information that participants receive about the fundamental value. Each experimental market is repeated three times. Throughout, we observe sizable bubbles that persist despite participant experience. Our findings in the call market experiment contrast with those in the literature. Our findings in the learning-to-forecast experiment are novel.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa121
ER  - 



